{
  "stem": "15721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a state senator, but he was also the international president of B'nai B'rith, and as such he had contacts in the State Department.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he called the State Department, and within a couple of hours I got back the message not to worry.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was not an action directed against my father, that it was a mass action.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The State Department official to whom Senator Cohen spoke assured him that therefore, everything would be OK, I shouldn't worry.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I had my mother's cable and I had this official reassurance that everything was going to be all right.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, it lasted a few days.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then, of course, the news was coming through.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My wrote me then a letter, too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My mother left Munich because she was afraid.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my school buddy, this Nordic tallest boy in the class-- Albert Klein was his name-- had joined the SS, that's the black shirts, mostly in order to camouflage his family, protect them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when he heard that my father had been taken to Dachau, he immediately put on his uniform and took my mother and my two brothers to the train station under SS escort, put them on a train to Stuttgart because my mother had a cousin in Stuttgart who was the consul of Panama and whose house in which the consulate was located, was therefore extraterritorial.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the idea was that that would be inviolate and the Nazis would not touch at that time, as yet, a foreign what shall we call them, representative.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so my mother and my two younger brothers spent several months there until my father was released from Dachau.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then in the meantime, efforts were made by my mother, who had two brothers in Brazil, to get them the necessary visa.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
